ed great wealth among speculatorswhereas as part of the great cabinets we want to improve the relationship with great britainwhereas later in the running to be president i suffered a strokeeven though i did suffer a stroke i am still a great political leader i have great views and beliefs i do believe i can bring this nation to great successgeneral political atmosphere –• all candidates were democraticrepublicans marking the end of the republicanfederalist political party•  election said to be the beginning of the  party systemissueso monroe doctrineo western expansiono suffrage for white menpolitical background• his political career started in  when he was appointed to write digest of georgia laws• in  he won a seat in the georgia legislature• in  he went to washington to fill the seat of the deceased senator abraham baldwin• he was elected to a full term as senator in • when vice president george clinton died in  he was elected president pro tempore of the senate• in  he was appointed secretary of war by james madison• the next year he became secretary of treasuryeconomic policy•in  congress chartered the bank of the united states for twenty years•in  the bank had to be rechartered – march   was the expiration date –gallatin secretary of treasury urged to recharter bank many opponents and complications• crawford promoted the first bank of the us in  – supported the bank system – thought it was dangerous to let the big states rule the country – believed the power of tax belonged to the states• recharted in personal background• william h crawford was born in amherst county virginia on february   the sixth kid out of  born to joel crawford and fanny harris crawford when crawford was  years old the family moved to edgefield south carolina and  years later to columbus county georgia after his father’s death in  crawford split time teaching school and farming as he tried to support his family for  years• crawford then went and moved to augusta to attend moses waddles carmel academy for  years he then became principal at one of the largest schools in augusta studied law and was admitted to the georgia bar in  crawford became a lawyer a year later and opened a law practice in lexington georgia• interested in politics more than laws he then went to complete a digest of the georgia laws of  to william h crawfordamerican bank systemslavery  native americansstrongly in support of slavery owned  slavesbelieved in sending all freed slaves back to africalike andrew jackson wanted to push the native americans off the land that was theirs because they were killing colonistsforeign policysupported president madisons embargo against great britain  franceserved as us minister to france for  yearslater became secretary of warcrawfords criticismcriticism on the american bank systemsecond bankmany state governments regarded the national bank as unresponsive to local needs and many western settlers and urban worker’s remembered bitterly the bank’s conservative credits policies during the panic of crawford was seen as “enemy to the principle of scattering banks profusely over the whole surface of the interior”first bankrepublican opponents of the bank particularly the south believed that the bank was an “unconstitutional manifestation of federal power dangerous to democratic institutions”criticism on foreign policypeople did not want to go into war and therefore not agreeing with the embargo act being removedfederalists believed that war would be almost as unpopular as the embargonot many agreed that war was the only alternative to the embargoother candidates weaknessesjacksonresented national bankmurdererclayhalfeducated gambler alcoholic and womanizeramerican system argued unconstitutional and creates unwanted competition in the westquincy adamsdirty deal with claycold personality and not socialfull transcriptpopular presentationssee more popular or the latest prezisproductcompanycareerssupportcommunitycontactapps english español 한국어  deutsch português français magyar italiano   prezi inc  termsconnect your facebook account to prezi and publish your likes in the future okno thanks william h crawford  united states government official  britannicacom encyclopædia britannica subscribe log in · join spotlight demystified quizzes galleries lists on this day biographies search britannica what are you looking for search browse popular topics dunkirk evacuation pangea truth cold war sir isaac newton william h crawfordunited states government official written by the editors of encyclopædia britannica see article history alternative title william harris crawford william h crawford united states government official also known aswilliam harris crawfordbornfebruary  amherst virginiadiedseptember   aged elberton georgiatitle  officesenate united states political affiliationdemocraticrepublican party view biographies related to categories government dates february  september  related biographies henry clay albert gallatin thomas jefferson james monroe charles pinckney john quincy adams aaron burr daniel d tompkins james madison martin van buren william h crawford born feb   amherst county now nelson county virginia—died sept   elberton ga us american political leader of the early us republic he finished third in electoral votes in the fourcandidate race for president in after living in virginia and south carolina the crawford family moved to georgia where william attended moses waddel’s carmel academy he then taught school in augusta studied law and in  opened a law practice in lexington ga a jeffersonian republican he entered elective politics in  winning a seat in the georgia legislature in  he went to washington to fill the unexpired term of georgia’s deceased us senator abraham baldwin in the senate crawford quickly earned a reputation for wisdom and sound judgment and the georgia legislature elected him to a full term as senator in  crawford backed us preparations for and the declaration of war against britain in  and—unlike most democratic republicans—favoured a tariff and extension of the charter of the bank of the united states when vice president george clinton died in  crawford was elected president pro tempore of the senate which his predecessor baldwin had been but left the position the following year to become minister to francein  president james madison appointed crawford secretary of war and a year later named him secretary of the treasury a position in which from  to  crawford’s abilities were best utilized a leading candidate for the presidential nomination in  crawford deferred to james monroe who was elected and who retained crawford as secretary of the treasury monroe was reelected virtually without opposition in  in  crawford was again a presidential prospect along with john quincy adams henry clay and andrew jacksoncrawford won the vote of the party caucus but by  the caucus system had fallen into disrepute and its choice proved meaningless at the time of the election crawford was paralyzed and nearly blind as the result of a stroke although his supporters claimed that he was steadily improving he finished a distant third behind adams and jacksoncrawford refused adams’ invitation to stay on as secretary of the treasury and instead returned to georgia where he served as a judge until his death learn more in these related articles presidency of the united states of america “king caucus”caucus by  it had fallen into such disrepute that only onefourth of the democraticrepublican congressional delegation took part in the caucus that nominated secretary of the treasury william read this article john quincy adams presidency and feud with jacksonclose in  there was a lack of good feeling among his official advisers three of whom—secretary of state john quincy adams secretary of war john c calhoun and secretary of the treasury will read this article united states presidential election of  the demise of “king caucus”the king caucus system had fallen into such disrepute that only onefourth of the democraticrepublican congressional delegation took part in the caucus which nominated secretary of the treasury w read this article in virginia constituent state of the united states of america one of the original  colonies it is bordered by maryland to the northeast the atlantic ocean to the southeast north carolinaread this article in members of the us senate the senate is one of the two houses of the bicameral united states congress established in  by the constitution of the united states it shares equal responsibility for lawmakingread this article in senate one of the two houses of the legislature congress of the united states established in  under the constitution each state elects two senators for sixyear terms the termsread this article in democraticrepublican party first opposition political party in the united states organized in  as the republican party its members held power nationally between  and  it was the direct antecedentread this article in georgia geographical and historical treatment of georgia including maps and a survey of its people economy and governmentread this article in united states country in north america a federal republic of  states besides the  conterminous states that occupy the middle latitudes of the continent the united states includes theread this article additional media more about william h crawford  references found in britannica articlesassorted referencescrawfordsville in crawfordsville presidential election of  in united states presidential election of  democraticrepublican victory presidential election of  in john quincy adams presidency and feud with jackson in democraticrepublican party in presidency of the united states of america “king caucus” in united states presidential election of  the demise of “king caucus” external links biographical directory of the united states congress  biography of william harris crawford new georgia encyclopedia  history and archaeology  biography of william ha