ngea truth cold war sir isaac newton william h crawfordunited states government official written by the editors of encyclopædia britannica see article history alternative title william harris crawford william h crawford united states government official also known aswilliam harris crawfordbornfebruary  amherst virginiadiedseptember   aged elberton georgiatitle  officesenate united states political affiliationdemocraticrepublican party view biographies related to categories government dates february  september  related biographies henry clay albert gallatin thomas jefferson james monroe charles pinckney john quincy adams aaron burr daniel d tompkins james madison martin van buren william h crawford born feb   amherst county now nelson county virginia—died sept   elberton ga us american political leader of the early us republic he finished third in electoral votes in the fourcandidate race for president in after living in virginia and south carolina the crawford family moved to georgia where william attended moses waddel’s carmel academy he then taught school in augusta studied law and in  opened a law practice in lexington ga a jeffersonian republican he entered elective politics in  winning a seat in the georgia legislature in  he went to washington to fill the unexpired term of georgia’s deceased us senator abraham baldwin in the senate crawford quickly earned a reputation for wisdom and sound judgment and the georgia legislature elected him to a full term as senator in  crawford backed us preparations for and the declaration of war against britain in  and—unlike most democratic republicans—favoured a tariff and extension of the charter of the bank of the united states when vice president george clinton died in  crawford was elected president pro tempore of the senate which his predecessor baldwin had been but left the position the following year to become minister to francein  president james madison appointed crawford secretary of war and a year later named him secretary of the treasury a position in which from  to  crawford’s abilities were best utilized a leading candidate for the presidential nomination in  crawford deferred to james monroe who was elected and who retained crawford as secretary of the treasury monroe was reelected virtually without opposition in  in  crawford was again a presidential prospect along with john quincy adams henry clay and andrew jacksoncrawford won the vote of the party caucus but by  the caucus system had fallen into disrepute and its choice proved meaningless at the time of the election crawford was paralyzed and nearly blind as the result of a stroke although his supporters claimed that he was steadily improving he finished a distant third behind adams and jacksoncrawford refused adams’ invitation to stay on as secretary of the treasury and instead returned to georgia where he served as a judge until his death learn more in these related articles presidency of the united states of america “king caucus”caucus by  it had fallen into such disrepute that only onefourth of the democraticrepublican congressional delegation took part in the caucus that nominated secretary of the treasury william read this article john quincy adams presidency and feud with jacksonclose in  there was a lack of good feeling among his official advisers three of whom—secretary of state john quincy adams secretary of war john c calhoun and secretary of the treasury will read this article united states presidential election of  the demise of “king caucus”the king caucus system had fallen into such disrepute that only onefourth of the democraticrepublican congressional delegation took part in the caucus which nominated secretary of the treasury w read this article in virginia constituent state of the united states of america one of the original  colonies it is bordered by maryland to the northeast the atlantic ocean to the southeast north carolinaread this article in members of the us senate the senate is one of the two houses of the bicameral united states congress established in  by the constitution of the united states it shares equal responsibility for lawmakingread this article in senate one of the two houses of the legislature congress of the united states established in  under the constitution each state elects two senators for sixyear terms the termsread this article in democraticrepublican party first opposition political party in the united states organized in  as the republican party its members held power nationally between  and  it was the direct antecedentread this article in georgia geographical and historical treatment of georgia including maps and a survey of its people economy and governmentread this article in united states country in north america a federal republic of  states besides the  conterminous states that occupy the middle latitudes of the continent the united states includes theread this article additional media more about william h crawford  references found in britannica articlesassorted referencescrawfordsville in crawfordsville presidential election of  in united states presidential election of  democraticrepublican victory presidential election of  in john quincy adams presidency and feud with jackson in democraticrepublican party in presidency of the united states of america “king caucus” in united states presidential election of  the demise of “king caucus” external links biographical directory of the united states congress  biography of william harris crawford new georgia encyclopedia  history and archaeology  biography of william harris crawford spartacus educational  biography of william crawford britannica web sites articles from britannica encyclopedias for elementary and high school studentswilliam harris crawford  student encyclopedia ages  and up an american political leader of the early us republic was william harris crawford known for his wisdom and sound judgment crawford served as us senator and as a cabinet member during the admin